args:
While the prince and friends look into a village
that was attacked by the dragon, Elisanne and
Alex follow the former Dyrenell solider who is
spreading rumors and learn a priest has been
pulling strings behind the scenes, leading to
a fight with the former solider.
(If I seek a place where rumors spread,\na bustling area in a local town would be\na logical starting point.)
(Another failure would be inexcusable in\nHis Highness's eyes; I MUST catch the\noffender.)
You never change, Elisanne.\nYou know this, yes?
Alex! How long have you been there?!
You didn't realize I was here? I swear,\nyou will cling to your serious nature until\nyou lie cold and still in the grave.
I can't very well leave you alone and let\nyou get yourself into trouble, so I sought\nthe prince's permission to come.
Thank you, Alex.\nI am ever indebted to you.
I think we can leave the formality by the\nwayside, don't you? More importantly,\nwhat's your read on these rumors?
The speed of their spread is no accident;\nI believe it likely that some organization is\nworking to see them swiftly propagated.

Additionally, we have the fact that Ciella
went out of her way to inform me of them.
When one put those two items together,
an inescapable conclusion comes to mind.

You suspect the Church. A sad thought,
that. Though I cannot deny there has been
disturbing activity coming from their
direction of late.
I pray my fears prove unfounded.\nBut for the nonce, I will attempt to\nfollow the flow of rumor in town.
Step lightly, Elisanne. If people realize\nwho we are, it will lead to trouble.
Hey there. Do you have a second to talk?\nI'd like to ask you about the damage\ncaused by the void dragon.
And there goes another one... *sigh*\nWe'll never be able to gather information\nif people flee in terror at our approach.
I can't BELIEVE all these jerks think\n{player_name} is the Other!
It's all right, Notte—it's my fault things\nhave ended up like this in the first place.
I was so caught up in defeating the Other\nand saving Zethia that I didn't notice what\na sad state the country had fallen into.
Almost without my noticing, the people's\nhearts have drifted away from both myself\nand the rest of the royal family.
We mustn't be discouraged; I'm certain we\nwill find someone willing to speak with us.
Say, I remember you! You used to come\nplay at the Halidom some time ago.\nHow have you been?
I'm great! But I've been sad that I couldn't\ngo play at the Halidom...
Ah, yes, we've been away a lot lately.\nAnd you're not scared of me?
Nope! There's no way you're the Other!\nBut nobody believes me when I tell them...
I appreciate your trust. Tell me though,\nhave you heard anything about a void\ndragon that attacked this village?
Yeah! This big black dragon swooped in\na week ago, and then a bunch of water\ncame and everybody ran away!
Sounds like a water dragon to me, though\nit doesn't explain why it showed up out of\nthe clear blue sky like that.
Yes, while void dragons are often frenzied,\nthey rarely appear near populated areas.
Something must have been driving it.\nWe need to learn more.
...So basically, the prince has been\npossessed by the Other.
If that's the case, he could come attack\nour village at any moment. I gotta hurry\nand warn the others!
Aye, set a watch and keep it close.\nBut now, I must be off.
That is clearly the cur responsible for\nspreading these baseless rumors.
He's leaving that shop as we speak;\nlet's follow and see where he goes.
It's the talk of the whole town, Captain.\nAs for me, I await your next order.

Heh, I'm not your ＂captain＂ anymore,
remember? Anyway, go to the
next village and seed the word there too.
I'm heading to see the priest.
That other man is clearly a former Dyrenell\nsoldier—and he's off to talk with a priest!
My fear has borne bitter fruit.
(Who is the priest in this region anyway?\nWasn't it...? No. It CAN'T be!)
Do you want me to head back to the\nChurch and seek further instruction?
(Alex is correct: My duty as a Paladyn\nis to inform the Church of this at once.)

(If it becomes known that these groundless
rumors are spreading because of someone
affiliated with the Church, its authority will
be greatly shaken.)
(Yet I cannot permit someone spreading\nsuch falsehoods about the prince to\ncontinue unchecked.)
Who is it that you believe, Elisanne?\nThe false prince? The deceitful Church?
Oh, I know that look—you want to go\nrunning off on your own again.
And what would you have me do\nduring your alone time, mmm?
Job's done, and done thoroughly.\nMy subordinates were happy to assist.
Here is remuneration for your services.\nIt is not much, but I pray you use it to\nmake a better life for your families.
Thanks, we can sure use it.\nBut if I may, why'd you want us to spread\nthis rumor abo—
So it was you, Father Marko.
Ah, Elisanne. It has been some time.\nYou have my gratitude for the assistance\nwith food distribution back then.

Father, why have you done this thing?
You only ever cared to become close
with the people of this region and bring
them word of Ilia's salvation, but now...

Though my actions may not seem laudable,
I can no longer turn a blind eye to a royal
family that cares not one whit for the
plight of its common people.
You hear the truth in my words, child—\nI know you do. So join us!
Together, we will create a new land where\nall support each other under the rich\nblessings of the Goddess!
......\nYour heart o'erflows with love for the\npeople, which is a precious thing indeed.
But I serve His Highness, and as such,\nI hereby arrest you in his name!
That is most unfortunate. ...Sir, pray\nforgive this request, but I fear I will\nneed you to deal with this woman.
You want me to take on a Grand Paladyn?\nThat won't come cheap.
Elisanne! I summoned the prince,\njust as you asked!
Hey! That's the chump what's been behind\nspreadin' all them nasty rumors around!\nIt's time to pay the fiddler, pal!
Heh, if it isn't the Other's loyal band.\nFine, then. I'll take you all on at once!
